description: Schibsted ASA engages in the provision of print and online media services. The company is headquartered in Oslo, Oslo and currently employs 5,182 full-time employees.  The Group is organized within two operating segments: Marketplaces and Media. The Marketplaces segment comprises online classifieds operations in Norway and Sweden, including FINN.no and Blocket.se. The Media segment consists of publishing operations in Norway and Sweden, including VG, Aftenposten, Stavanger Aftenblad, Bergens Tidende, Faedrelandsvennen, Aftonbladet, Svenska Dagbladet and Omni, in addition to such companies as Lendo, Prisjakt, Let’s Deal, among others. The firm conducts its business through a net of subsidiaries located worldwide and distributes its products in Europe, Asia, Africa and the Americas. The firm owns Yapo.cl. and a share in OLX Brazil, among others.
